# hpm-manufacturing-tool Debian Package

Debian packaging for [HPMicro Manufacturing Tool](https://github.com/hpmicro/hpm_manufacturing_tool) v0.6.0 — GUI and CLI tools for programming and signing HPMicro MCU devices via USB DFU.

## Install Location

| Path | Content |
|---|---|
| `/opt/hpm_manufacturing_tool/` | All binaries (`hpm_manufacturing_gui`, `hpm_manufacturing_cmd`, `hpm_image_helper`) |
| `/etc/profile.d/hpm_manufacturing_tool.sh` | PATH auto-configuration |

After install, re-login or `source /etc/profile.d/hpm_manufacturing_tool.sh` to add the tools to your PATH.

## Local Build

```bash
# Download and extract the upstream tarball
wget https://github.com/hpmicro/hpm_manufacturing_tool/releases/download/v0.6.0/HPMicro_Manufacturing_Tool_v0.6.0.tar.gz
tar -xzf HPMicro_Manufacturing_Tool_v0.6.0.tar.gz

# Build the .deb (binary-only, unsigned)
sudo apt-get install -y build-essential debhelper
dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc -b

# Output: ../hpm-manufacturing-tool_0.6.0-1_amd64.deb
```

## CI/CD

Push to any branch triggers `.github/workflows/build-deb.yml`:

1. Downloads upstream tarball from HPMicro releases
2. Builds `.deb` via `dpkg-buildpackage`
3. Uploads artifact
4. If pushed with a `v*` tag, creates a GitHub Release with the `.deb`

Manual trigger via `workflow_dispatch` is also available.
